<h2 class=3D"wp-block-heading"><a></a>Does a Dog=E2=80=99s Breed Effect The=
ir Dog Years to Human Years Calculation?</h2>



<p>Mainly, it is just a dog=E2=80=99s size that determines the calculation =
of a dog=E2=80=99s dog years to human years. However, the life expectancy f=
or different dog breeds may be different, even if they are roughly the same=
 size. This difference in life expectancy is mainly due to <a href=3D"https=
://sports.yahoo.com/dog-breeds-most-health-problems-173436578.html" target=
=3D"_blank" rel=3D"noreferrer noopener" aria-label=3D"Opens in new window">=
health problems</a> affecting the breed. The healthier a breed tends to be,=
 the longer their life expectancy will be.</p>



<figure class=3D"wp-block-image size-large is-resized" role=3D"none"><img f=
